* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑmənd/}}, {{IPA|/ˈɑlmənd/}}, {{IPA|/æmənd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-almond.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A type of [[tree]] [[nut]].
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A small [[deciduous]] tree, {{taxlink|Prunus dulcis|species|noshow=1}}, that produces almonds.
#* '''2004''', {{w|Richard Fortey}}, ''The Earth'', Folio Society 2011, p. 3:
#*: In early March the '''almonds''' are in flower, delicately pink, and there are washes of bright daffodils beneath the orchard trees; you can see women gathering them for market.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The [[colour]] of the [[kernel]] of an almond without its [[shell]] and thin [[seed coat]], a [[creamy]] off-[[white]] colour.
#: {{color panel|almond|FFEBCD}}<!--this is the hex tripled used for the X11 BlanchedAlmond color-->
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The color of an almond still covered by its skin, a shade of brown.
#: {{color panel|almond|A67B5B}}

